						<summary>

						<p>Stone in a field known as <hi rend="bold"><hi rend="italic">āvula-doḍḍi-gaḍḍa.</hi></hi></p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1476, Ānanda, Pushya śu 1 Sunday, Makara-Saṁkrānti</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1554 A.D., January 3,</hi> however the day was <hi rend="bold">Wednesday.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records the construction of a canal in the name of his mother, Kāvēramma by Narasanāyaka, son of Kasavināyaka, who was the mace-bearer of the <hi rend="italic">Mahāmaṇḍaleśvara</hi> Mēdinimisara-gaṁda Kaṭhāri-sāluva Immaḍi Narasiṁharāya Mahārāya.</p>						

						</summary>
